name: E-Cell 2024
description: E-Summit, CRESCENT INSTITUTE OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY, flagship event, focuses on young entrepreneurs and their venture and is an entrepreneurial extravaganza filled with an insane amount of energy and enthusiasm. There is something for every one to gain and learn from complete entrepreneurship to startup founders. With more then 30 speakers, 10 startups, 25 investors and over 500 attendees, E-Summit is truly one of the finest learning opportunities for attendees and other stakeholders.

competitions.title: Shark Tank
competitions.description:
Pitch your game-changing idea or product to potential investors! Form a team, get creative, and prepare for a 15-minute presentation with Q&A. Dive into the tank and make your pitch unforgettable!

RULES

  • Participants can form a group of 1-5 members.
  • The group must submit their idea template/actual product 20 days before the event for verification by CIIC & CISC members.
  • Once the product is approved by our team, participants will be allowed to participate.
  • Presentation/pitch time must be less than 15 minutes.
  • If investors are satisfied, discussions will be initiated.
  • Participants must have knowledge of equity share, profit, loss, and other business-related parameters of their company/product.

competitions.title: On spot promotion
competitions.description:
By participating in our mini hackathon, you'll have the chance to showcase your talents, learn from peers, and potentially win exciting prizes while contributing to the advancement of technology and innovation. We look forward to you participation and the amazing ideas that will emerge during this event.

Rules

  • Only individual participation is encouraged.
  • Participants must pitch the product provided by us on the spot.
  • There will be a time limit of 8 minutes per participant.
  • Participants must use their creative skills to pitch the product.
  • The product will be given to them an hour before the actual pitch for preparation.

competitions.title: StockMaster Challenge
competitions.description: By participating in our mini hackathon, you'll have the chance to showcase your talents, learn from peers, and potentially win exciting prizes while contributing to the advancement of technology and innovation. We look forward to you participation and the amazing ideas that will emerge during this event.

competitions.title: Pitch-X Challenge
competitions.description:
An exciting opportunity for participants to showcase their marketing and pitching skills in a dynamic and competitive environment.

Rules

  • The product to pitch will be given on spot.
  • Participants will be given 2-5 mins time to prepare for their pitch.
  • Each participants will have strict time limit to deliver their pitch.
  • Participants will be judged on several criteria,including creativity, persuasiveness, clarity, audience engagement, and adherence to time limits.
  • Plagiarism or using pre-prepared pitches will result in disqualification.

competitions.title: Reverse Engineering Challenge
competitions.description:
Recreation Challenge, where innovation meets improvement! In this unique competition, participants are tasked with taking an existing product and enhancing it to propose strategies for boosting sales. Get ready to put your creativity, marketing prowess, and problem-solving skills to the test as you revamp products.

Rules

  • Product Selection: Choose an existing market-available product for improvement.
  • Enhancement Proposal: Outline plans for product improvements, including new features and modifications.
  • Sales Strategy: Propose a comprehensive marketing plan targeting specific audiences and utilizing various channels.
  • Presentation: Present product enhancements and sales strategy within a set time to judges.
  • Product will be evaluated based on creativity, feasibility, potential for sales improvement.

competitions.title: Bizlens Expo
competitions.description:
Calling all talented photographers and videographers! Join us for the BizLens Ad Creation Competition, where you'll have the opportunity tocraft compelling advertisements for various startups. Each winning team will be rewarded with cash prizes generously provided by the startups themselves. The top ad, selected by the startups, will earn an additional cash prize. Don't miss this chance to showcase your creative prowess and win big!

Rules

  • Participants receive designated time to capture original photos based on assigned concepts
  • Using these photos, participants create advertisements for various formats, such as print, social media, and multimedia.
  • All content must adhere to ethical guidelines, ensuring it remains non-offensive, nondiscriminatory, and copyright-compliant.
  • Submissions are required within specified time frames.

competitions.title: E-Mergence & Project Expo
competitions.description:
Students hailing from various colleges, each equipped with their own entrepreneurship cell, are invited to join us at E-Emergence. This unique gathering serves as a platform for sharing diverse information and ideas, fostering collaboration and innovation within the entrepreneurial community. Students are encouraged to participate by presenting their innovations and diverse projects at this project expo, offering them an opportunity not only to showcase their work but also to compete for a range of exciting prizes.

Rule

  • Projects must be submitted before the deadline and will be validated by our experts
  • Participants will have designated presentation slots in the networking arena.
  • Networking and collaboration with fellow attendees is encouraged to enhance project potential and positively influence the selection process.
  • Projects will be voted on by fellow attendees, and the one with the most likes or positive feedback will be declared the winner.

competitions.title: THE 6-HOUR BUSINESS HACK
competitions.description:
We invite you to be a part of our Mini Hackathon, a dynamic 6-hour event where participants will tackle real-world business challenges and data-driven problems. This intensive competition offers a unique opportunity to apply your problem-solving skills and creativity. Join us for a day of innovation, teamwork, and hands-on problem-solving at our Mini Hackathon.

Rules

  • Team Formation: Participants can choose to work solo or form teams of 2-4 members. Teams can be pre-formed or assembled at the event
  • Challenge Themes: The hackathon may have specific themes or challenges that participants must address in their projects, sparking creativity and innovation.
  • Time Limit: Participants will have a defined time frame (6 hours) to ideate, code, and develop their projects, starting and ending at specified times
  • Coding Tools: Participants are free to use any programming languages, development frameworks, or tools they prefer.
  • Judging Criteria: Projects will be assessed based on creativity, functionality, usability, adherence to the theme, and overall effectiveness.
  • Presentation: Each team or participant will have a limited time (e.g., 5-7 minutes) to present their project to a panel of judges or the audience.
  • Code of Conduct: Participants are expected to follow a code of conduct that promotes ethical behavior, teamwork, and respect.
